# 3. フェスの心得

Honami: Nice work, everyone. Let's keep up this momentum as we prepare for the festival.
Saki: Okay! Get home safe, you guys!
Saki: *Sigh* Today's practice was really tough, but also really fun!
Saki: I can't wait for Jam Fest...
Saki: (It's the biggest venue we've ever played at, so I hope a ton of people come to see us there.)
Saki: (Plus, it's gonna be our first show since going pro, so we gotta do a good job...!)
Saki: (Still, I can't help but feel a little nervous, since this is also gonna be our first big festival...)
Saki: (It's probably gonna feel different from the joint and solo shows we've done until now...)
Saki: (Is it really okay for us to prepare for it just by practicing like we always do?)
???: Okay, see you tomorrow.
???: Alright, bye!
Saki: Huh? That sounded like...
Saki: Iori?!
Iori: Huh...?
Iori: Wait, you're...
Saki: Oh, I'm sorry for calling out your name all of a sudden! I'm Saki Tenma from Leo/need!
Saki: So, I don't know if you remember me, but you've helped us quite a lot and...
Iori: Oh, you're that keyboardist. The girl who's always having so much fun while she plays.
Saki: Wait, you remember who I am?! Thank you so much!
Saki: Also, do I really play like that?
Iori: Yeah, Leo/need always looks like it's having fun, but I feel like you usually have the most fun.
Iori: And I get to have fun watching.
Saki: Hehe...
Iori: Come to think of it, Leo/need's playing at Jam Fest, right? I'm looking forward to seeing you all there.
Saki: Yes, likewise!
Saki: Oh, Iori, while we're on the subject, can I ask you a quick question?
Iori: Hm? Sure.
Saki: Umm... What's it like to play at a big music festival?
Saki: This is gonna be our first one... So, if possible, can you tell me more about them?
Iori: Oh, that's right. Alright, so...
Iori: For starters, depending on the size of the festival, you'll be dealing with a lot more people than normal. Tens of thousands even.
Saki: Th-That many?!
Iori: However, not everyone in attendance will be there to see us.
Iori: Loads of them will be people who have never heard of us, who are here for other bands.
Iori: There's a chance folks like that, who don't have any interest in us, might leave when we take the stage.
Iori: Especially if there's a famous band also playing during your timeslot, you might not get any people watching at all. That happens.
Saki: Oh...
Iori: That's why you have to put on a performance that'll grab people, and make them think twice before leaving.
Iori: Easier said than done.
Saki: Right... Shiho even said that a lot of people are gonna be focused on the main stage.
Iori: Exactly.
Iori: But getting people to stop and listen after they've already written you off...
Iori: Drawing them in with your music when that's what you're up against? It's the best feeling in the world.
Saki: ...!
Saki: (That's what I felt when we played with anemone...)
Saki: (It's impossibly hard to convince people who aren't interested to stay.)
Saki: (But...)
Saki: (When you see your song getting through to them... It really is the best feeling in the world...!)
Saki: Um, Iori! Can you tell me about how we should prepare?!
Iori: Huh?
Saki: I want us to succeed no matter what!
Saki: This is going to be Leo/need's first show since going pro, so I wanna reach as many people as we can with our songs!
Iori: Tenma...
Iori: Then, since we're here, why don't we grab a quick bite together?
Saki: What? A-As in a meal?!
Iori: Yeah, I'm sure you worked up an appetite during practice.
Iori: Plus, you released a new song recently. I'd like to hear more about it, so it'll be my treat.
Saki: No, you don't have to...!
Iori: It's fine. You want to hear what I have to say, right? So, let's go.
Saki: Uhh... R-Right! Thank you very much!
